# Valor vem do .env (API_BASE_URL); @baseUrl é o nome que o REST Client resolve em {{baseUrl}}
@baseUrl = {{$dotenv API_BASE_URL}}

### Auth - Register
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "brunogameplay",
  "email": "ubruno@example.com",
  "password": "123456"
}

### Auth - Login
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "brunogameplay",
  "password": "123456"
}

### Auth - Get Users For Auth
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/users

### Auth - Get User By ID
# id é UUID (ver entidade User). Ex.: "1" faz o Postgres rejeitar e antes dava 500.
# Substitua por um id real: SELECT id FROM users LIMIT 1;
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/users/a1b2c3d4-0001-4000-8000-000000000001